      public Collection(File file) throws IOException
      Converts a given Collection in text notation into a Collection.
      Parameters:
      file - A file containing the collection in text notation.
      Throws:
      InvalidSyntaxException - If the String does not contain a Collection or if it contains an invalid key (or two equal keys).
      IOException - If it is not possible to read the file.

      public Collection remove(String key, int index)
